items.title: Awesome Python Data Science
items.content_text:
### Machine Learning / General Purpose Machine Learning

*   [xLearn (‚≠ê3.1k)](https://github.com/aksnzhy/xlearn) - High Performance, Easy-to-use, and Scalable Machine Learning Package.
*   [mlpack (‚≠ê5.4k)](https://github.com/mlpack/mlpack) - A scalable C++ machine learning library (Python bindings).
*   [pyGAM (‚≠ê898)](https://github.com/dswah/pyGAM) - Generalized Additive Models in Python.

### Machine Learning / Kernel Methods

*   [liquidSVM (‚≠ê67)](https://github.com/liquidSVM/liquidSVM) - An implementation of SVMs.

### Model Explanation / Others

*   [Alibi (‚≠ê2.5k)](https://github.com/SeldonIO/alibi) - Algorithms for monitoring and explaining machine learning models.
*   [anchor (‚≠ê804)](https://github.com/marcotcr/anchor) - Code for "High-Precision Model-Agnostic Explanations" paper.
*   [aequitas (‚≠ê725)](https://github.com/dssg/aequitas) - Bias and Fairness Audit Toolkit.
*   [ELI5 (‚≠ê2.8k)](https://github.com/TeamHG-Memex/eli5) - A library for debugging/inspecting machine learning classifiers and explaining their predictions.
*   [L2X (‚≠ê124)](https://github.com/Jianbo-Lab/L2X) - Code for replicating the experiments in the paper *Learning to Explain: An Information-Theoretic Perspective on Model Interpretation*.
*   [PDPbox (‚≠ê860)](https://github.com/SauceCat/PDPbox) - Partial dependence plot toolbox.
*   [PyCEbox (‚≠ê165)](https://github.com/AustinRochford/PyCEbox) - Python Individual Conditional Expectation Plot Toolbox.
*   [Skater](https://github.com/datascienceinc/Skater) - Python Library for Model Interpretation.
*   [AI Explainability 360 (‚≠ê1.7k)](https://github.com/IBM/AIX360) - Interpretability and explainability of data and machine learning models.

### Genetic Programming / Others

*   [DEAP (‚≠ê6.1k)](https://github.com/DEAP/deap) - Distributed Evolutionary Algorithms in Python.
*   [monkeys (‚≠ê125)](https://github.com/hchasestevens/monkeys) - A strongly-typed genetic programming framework for Python.

### Optimization / Others

*   [Spearmint (‚≠ê1.6k)](https://github.com/HIPS/Spearmint) - Bayesian optimization.
*   [SMAC3 (‚≠ê1.2k)](https://github.com/automl/SMAC3) - Sequential Model-based Algorithm Configuration.
*   [Optunity (‚≠ê421)](https://github.com/claesenm/optunity) - Is a library containing various optimizers for hyperparameter tuning.
*   [hyperopt (‚≠ê7.4k)](https://github.com/hyperopt/hyperopt) - Distributed Asynchronous Hyperparameter Optimization in Python.
*   [SafeOpt (‚≠ê147)](https://github.com/befelix/SafeOpt) - Safe Bayesian Optimization.
*   [scikit-optimize (‚≠ê2.8k)](https://github.com/scikit-optimize/scikit-optimize) - Sequential model-based optimization with a `scipy.optimize` interface.
*   [Solid (‚≠ê579)](https://github.com/100/Solid) - A comprehensive gradient-free optimization framework written in Python.
*   [PySwarms (‚≠ê1.3k)](https://github.com/ljvmiranda921/pyswarms) - A research toolkit for particle swarm optimization in Python.
*   [Platypus (‚≠ê615)](https://github.com/Project-Platypus/Platypus) - A Free and Open Source Python Library for Multiobjective Optimization.
*   [POT (‚≠ê2.6k)](https://github.com/rflamary/POT) - Python Optimal Transport library.
*   [Talos (‚≠ê1.6k)](https://github.com/autonomio/talos) - Hyperparameter Optimization for Keras Models.
*   [nlopt (‚≠ê2.1k)](https://github.com/stevengj/nlopt) - Library for nonlinear optimization (global and local, constrained or unconstrained).

### Statistics / NLP

*   [scikit-posthocs (‚≠ê369)](https://github.com/maximtrp/scikit-posthocs) - Pairwise Multiple Comparisons Post-hoc Tests.

### Evaluation / Synthetic Data

*   [recmetrics (‚≠ê579)](https://github.com/statisticianinstilettos/recmetrics) - Library of useful metrics and plots for evaluating recommender systems.
*   [Metrics (‚≠ê1.6k)](https://github.com/benhamner/Metrics) - Machine learning evaluation metric.

### Computations / Synthetic Data

*   [numpy](http://www.numpy.org/) - The fundamental package needed for scientific computing with Python.
*   [bottleneck (‚≠ê1.1k)](https://github.com/kwgoodman/bottleneck) - Fast NumPy array functions written in C.
*   [CuPy (‚≠ê10k)](https://github.com/cupy/cupy) - NumPy-like API accelerated with CUDA.
*   [scikit-tensor (‚≠ê406)](https://github.com/mnick/scikit-tensor) - Python library for multilinear algebra and tensor factorizations.
*   [numdifftools (‚≠ê266)](https://github.com/pbrod/numdifftools) - Solve automatic numerical differentiation problems in one or more variables.
*   [quaternion (‚≠ê637)](https://github.com/moble/quaternion) - Add built-in support for quaternions to numpy.
*   [adaptive (‚≠ê1.2k)](https://github.com/python-adaptive/adaptive) - Tools for adaptive and parallel samping of mathematical functions.

### Spatial Analysis / Synthetic Data

*   [PySal (‚≠ê1.4k)](https://github.com/pysal/pysal) - Python Spatial Analysis Library.

### Quantum Computing / Synthetic Data

*   [QML (‚≠ê205)](https://github.com/qmlcode/qml) - A Python Toolkit for Quantum Machine Learning.

### Conversion / Synthetic Data

*   [ONNX (‚≠ê19k)](https://github.com/onnx/onnx) - Open Neural Network Exchange.
*   [MMdnn (‚≠ê5.8k)](https://github.com/Microsoft/MMdnn) -  A set of tools to help users inter-operate among different deep learning frameworks.
